To install zeek you will need an internet connection to the kit. open a terminal and follow the below steps. Run the following commands in the terminal sesson:
sudo su
yum install epel-release -y
yum installpython3-Gitpython pip3 pip-python libmaxminddb sendmail curl gperftools jemalloc PF_RING krb5 ipsumpdump curl git ntp chromium 
yum install centos-release-scl-rh
yum --enablerepo==centos-sclo-rh-resting install devtoolset-7
yum update 
yum upgrade
yum install cmake3 
scl enable devtoolset-7 bash
pip3 install cmake
pip3 install gitpython semantic-version
pip3 install zkg
pip3 install git+git://github.com/zeek/package-manager@master 
cd /etc/yum.repos.d/
wget https://download.opensuse.org/repositories/security:zeek/CentOS_7/security:zeek.repo
yum install zeek

**Next you have to use a text editor like vim or gedit to edit a few files. Instructions on editing are below. i used vim**
vim /opt/zeek/etc/networks.cfg
  :set number
  *go to line 8 and input the following:
  10.1.6.0/16     Kit 1
  10.1.7.0/16     Kit 2
  10.1.8.0/16     Kit 3
  *save and exit with :wq!
  
vim /opt/zeek/etc/node.cfg
  :set number
  *edit line 10 to be 10.1.x.20 where x is the kit subnet
  *edit line 11 to be em2
  :wq!
  
 **return to entering commands in the terminal**
 cd /opt/zeek/bin
 ./zeekctl
 **you will enter a zeekcontrol shell, continue to enter the following commands*
 install
 deploy
 **if it worked, enter the stop command and exit zeekctl shell. from now on run /opt/zeek/bin/zeekctl <command> to deploy, start, or stop zeek. **
 
cd /opt/zeek/bin 
./zeekctl stop
vim ../share/zeek/site/local.zeek
** at the bottom of the file, input the following **
  #Output to JSON
  @load policy/tuning/json-logs.zeek
  :wq!

@load policy/tuning/json-logs.zeek
